## When to use this pattern

Follow this pattern if you need to ask users in the UK for their ethnic group.


## How it works

You should:

- only collect users’ ethnic groups if the data will be used
- tell users how their data will be used
- use the ethnic group categories from the most recent census
- allow users to opt out
- allow users to write in their ethnicity
- ensure the data is used and stored in line with data protection rules

You should not:

- change any of the wording
- change the ordering of the categories

### Two step process

This pattern is designed to be split across 2 pages. The first page asks the user for their broad ethnic group. The second page allows users to choose from a more detailed breakdown of ethnicities within their broad group.  Users should only be able to select 1 option per page.

